.TH README-2-POST "1" "December 2025" "202602020740-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
readme-2-post \- Create a markdown file from a README file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B readme-2-post
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,README_FILE\/\fR] [\fI\,OUTPUT_FILE\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B readme-2-post
is a script for converting README files into blog post format. It transforms GitHub-style README files into markdown suitable for static site generators like Jekyll or Hugo.
.PP
The script can add front matter, adjust formatting, and prepare content for publication.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
